============================================================
ENV CONFIG
============================================================

Create `.env.example`:

APP_NAME=zDash
APP_ENV=development
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

BACKEND_HOST=0.0.0.0
BACKEND_PORT=8000

CLAUDE_API_KEY=
CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5
AI_PROVIDER=mock

DRY_RUN=true

============================================================
API RESPONSE FORMAT
============================================================

Every API must return:

{
  "ok": true,
  "data": {},
  "error": null,
  "timestamp": "ISO_DATE"
}

For errors:

{
  "ok": false,
  "data": null,
  "error": {
    "code": "ERROR_CODE",
    "message": "Human readable message"
  },
  "timestamp": "ISO_DATE"
}

Create helper functions in:

backend/app/core/responses.py

============================================================
AGENT RUNTIME REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create BaseAgent class with:

- id
- name
- role
- status
- metadata
- receive_message()
- run_task()
- emit_event()
- health_check()

Agent statuses:

- idle
- running
- error
- disabled

Create these agents:

1. CEO Agent
   - role: commander
   - can send message to Janie

2. Janie Agent
   - role: operator
   - receives CEO messages
   - calls AI adapter
   - returns response
   - emits event logs

============================================================
AI ADAPTER REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create interface:

AIAdapter:
  - generate_response(prompt: str, context: dict | None = None) -> AIResponse

Create:

1. MockAIAdapter
   - Always works
   - Used by default
   - Returns deterministic mock response

2. ClaudeAdapter
   - Reads CLAUDE_API_KEY and CLAUDE_MODEL from environment
   - If key missing, fallback to MockAIAdapter
   - Do not crash when key is missing
   - Keep implementation replaceable
   - If real Claude SDK is not installed, write safe placeholder structure and document where to connect it

============================================================
EVENT BUS REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create simple in-memory event bus for Phase 1:

Event fields:
- id
- type
- source
- message
- payload
- created_at

Event types:
- system.startup
- agent.message.received
- agent.message.sent
- ai.response.generated
- error

Add API endpoint to retrieve recent logs/events.

============================================================
REQUIRED API ENDPOINTS
============================================================

GET /health

Returns:
- app name
- environment
- status
- timestamp

GET /api/agents

Returns all registered agents and their health status.

POST /api/agents/message

Request body:

{
  "from_agent": "ceo",
  "to_agent": "janie",
  "message": "Hello Janie, report status.",
  "context": {}
}

Response:
- message id
- from_agent
- to_agent
- response text
- event ids
- timestamp

GET /api/logs

Returns recent event logs.

============================================================
TEST REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Write tests for:

1. Health endpoint works
2. Agents are registered
3. CEO can send message to Janie
4. Janie returns AI-generated mock response
5. Missing Claude key falls back to mock adapter
6. Event logs are created
7. API response format is consistent

All tests must pass with:

cd backend
pytest

============================================================
RUN COMMANDS
============================================================

Backend run command:

cd backend
uvicorn app.main:app --reload

Smoke test:

curl http://localhost:8000/health
curl http://localhost:8000/api/agents
curl http://localhost:8000/api/logs

Message test:

curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/agents/message \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "from_agent": "ceo",
    "to_agent": "janie",
    "message": "Hello Janie, report system status.",
    "context": {}
  }'

